@agentic_function # @agentic_function wraps a Python function whose body may run LLM calls through runtime.exec() . The wrapper records the function call in the session DAG unless expose="hidden" is used. This page explains the usage patterns. Metadata rules live in function-metadata.md . Basic pattern # from openprogram import agentic_function @agentic_function ( input = { "text" : { "description" : "Text to translate." }, }) def translate_to_chinese ( text : str , runtime = None ) -> str : """Translate text to Chinese.""" return runtime . exec ( content = [{ "type" : "text" , "text" : ( "Translate the following text to Chinese. Return only the translation. 

